{"id":14880720,"mediaExerciseId":"69418a88-a578-49f3-8cf8-747939f9acb0","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"1","chapterTitle":"Introduction To Corporate Finance","groupId":612257,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":18,"solutions":[{"id":5882296,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the goal that should always motivate the actions of a firm’s financial manager.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/4eab2327cb3d6f4563e1d3e900d554ee/ae34207ceff130e885c6320336457d05/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/4eab2327cb3d6f4563e1d3e900d554ee/ae34207ceff130e885c6320336457d05/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financial management.\n\n**Financial management** is a strategic planning, organizing, directing, and controlling of a company's finances.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/4eab2327cb3d6f4563e1d3e900d554ee/41cdb3d5e13b299a2e771f70e995dcb3/lateximg_large.png","width":993},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/4eab2327cb3d6f4563e1d3e900d554ee/41cdb3d5e13b299a2e771f70e995dcb3/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The actions of a firm’s financial manager should be motivated by the firm's goal to maximize the current market value of its equity, therefore maximizing shareholders' wealth.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/4eab2327cb3d6f4563e1d3e900d554ee/0cb55a15e866336b23b7019e2ccdc7df/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/14/4eab2327cb3d6f4563e1d3e900d554ee/0cb55a15e866336b23b7019e2ccdc7df/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"187706f0-62d7-458b-b943-ce3087ba4999","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3},{"id":6374946,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will explore the major goal of financial management and what goal should always motivate a company's financial manager's actions.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Financial management involves the planning, organizing, coordinating, and administration of a business's financial operations. Financial managers ensure that the company has enough cash on hand to pay suppliers and employees on time.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The major **goal of financial management** is to optimize the stock's current worth per share. Shareholders want to maximize their wealth, which is mostly determined by the price at which the shares are trading on the market. When there is a growth in the market price of the shares, there is a corresponding increase in the wealth of the shareholders, and vice versa. A company's financial manager is responsible for making choices that benefit the company's shareholders. He must execute financial choices that will be profitable for shareholders in the long run.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"However, this goal does not imply that the financial management should engage in illegal or immoral behavior in order to increase the firm's equity value. The best way for a financial manager to help the business owners is to identify goods and services that bring value to the company because they are desired and valued in the free market. Every financial manager's efforts are motivated by the principal goal of financial health.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"499698c8-457a-469c-ad91-05221991eef7","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880721,"exerciseName":"7","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"afbf8577-59fe-4c13-ae7d-d2964b0ba1da","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-7-afbf8577-59fe-4c13-ae7d-d2964b0ba1da"},{"id":14880722,"exerciseName":"8","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"63927895-23bb-4933-936f-404b659cf139","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-8-63927895-23bb-4933-936f-404b659cf139"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880719,"exerciseName":